My Downfall (Original Soundtrack) is an album by 

breakcore artist Venetian Snares. The title is 

in reference not to an actual soundtrack but 

rather the soundtrack to Aaron Funk's 

"downfall". It is said to be a follow-up to the 

2005 album Rossz csillag alatt szÃƒÂ¼letett, as 

hinted by the reappearing Hungarian song titles. 

Aaron was quoted as saying, "This album has 

nothing to do with dubstep and very little to do 

with breakcore." It, like the album it is said 

to follow, consists largely of classical 

compositions. However, unlike said album, it 

features very little in the way of drumbeats, 

instead focusing on an atmospheric sound made by 

the classical instruments.
